:Description\n        rdf:about=\"/abs/2607.05971\"\n        dc:identifier=\"/abs/2607.05971\"\n        dc:title=\"Multimodal Video-to-Music Recommendation via Semantic Retrieval and Temporal Reranking\"\n        trackback:ping=\"/trackback/2607.05971\" />\n    </rdf:RDF>\n--><div id=\"abs-outer\">\n\n  <div class=\"leftcolumn\">\n    <div class=\"subheader\">\n      <h1>Computer Science > Multimedia</h1>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"header-breadcrumbs-mobile\">\n      <strong>arXiv:2607.05971v1</strong> (cs)\n    </div>\n<link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"/static/base/1.0.1/css/abs.css\">\n<div id=\"content-inner\">\n  <div id=\"abs\">\n    <div class=\"dateline\">\n  [Submitted on 7 Jul 2026]</div>\n    <h1 class=\"title mathjax\"><span class=\"descriptor\">Title:</span>Multimodal Video-to-Music Recommendation via Semantic Retrieval and Temporal Reranking</h1>\n    <div class=\"authors\"><span class=\"descriptor\">Authors:</span><a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Doh,+S\" rel=\"nofollow\">Seungheon Doh</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Lee,+M\" rel=\"nofollow\">Minhee Lee</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Lee,+S\" rel=\"nofollow\">Sangmoon Lee</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Chon,+B+S\" rel=\"nofollow\">Ben Sangbae Chon</a>, <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/search/cs?searchtype=author&amp;query=Nam,+J\" rel=\"nofollow\">Juhan Nam</a></div>            <div id=\"download-button-info\" hidden>View a PDF of the paper titled Multimodal Video-to-Music Recommendation via Semantic Retrieval and Temporal Reranking, by Seungheon Doh and 4 other authors</div>\n    <a class=\"mobile-submission-download\" href=\"/pdf/2607.05971v1\">View PDF</a>\n    <a class=\"mobile-submission-download\" href=\"https://arxiv.org/html/2607.05971v1\">HTML (experimental)</a>\n\n\n\n    <blockquote class=\"abstract mathjax\">\n            <span class=\"descriptor\">Abstract:</span>We present VTMR, a two-stage framework for Video-To-Music Recommendation. In Stage~1, VTMR aligns comprehensive video and music signals in a joint audio-visual-text representation space and efficiently retrieves semantically compatible candidates using coarse global embeddings. In Stage~2, it reranks the retrieved candidates by attending to the temporal sequences of both video and music, thereby capturing fine-grained temporal correspondence. Evaluated on the video-to-music recommendation task, the multimodal retrieval stage improves R@10 from 14.2 to 15.9 and Median Rank from 75 to 58 over the strongest baseline; the temporal reranker further boosts R@10 to 18.3 and Median Rank to 46, demonstrating complementary gains from richer query encoding and temporal alignment. A human preference study confirms that VTMR is on par with a commercial baseline in overall preference, while outperforming a generative baseline in music quality.\n    </blockquote>\n\n    <!--CONTEXT-->\n    <div class=\"metatable\">\n      <table summary=\"Additional metadata\">        <tr>\n          <td class=\"tablecell label\">Comments:</td>\n          <td class=\"tablecell comments mathjax\">Accepted for publication at The Machine Learning for Audio workshop at ICML 2026</td>\n        </tr>\n<tr>\n          <td class=\"tablecell label\">Subjects:</td>\n          <td class=\"tablecell subjects\">\n            <span class=\"primary-subject\">Multimedia (cs.MM)</span>; Sound (cs.SD)</td>\n        </tr><tr>\n          <td class=\"tablecell label\">Cite as:</td>\n          <td class=\"tablecell arxivid\"><span class=\"arxivid\"><a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.05971\">arXiv:2607.05971</a> [cs.MM]</span></td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr>\n          <td class=\"tablecell label\">&nbsp;</td>\n          <td class=\"tablecell arxividv\">(or <span class=\"arxivid\">\n              <a href=\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2607.05971v1\">arXiv:2607.05971v1</a> [cs.MM]</sp